The specification of variables should be time dependent (cf. Pentz et al., 1996). For example, in a 5-year longitudinal study, it might be hypothesized that initial implementation of a prevention education program in a community during thefirst2 years is a catalyst for school district adoption of a policy in year 3 that guarantees set-aside funds, time, and teacher training for program implementation in later years. If this course of action is hypothesized a priori, then program implementation acts as an antecedent (independent) variable in years 1 and 2 to policy change in year 3, and policy change in year 3 is an antecedent to continued, and perhaps, improved, program implementation as a consequent (dependent) variable in years 4 and 5.
